We were visiting Pune for just a night and urgently needed rooms as we were a group of 9 people. Even though we had booked non-AC rooms, the ventilation was so good that the rooms remained pleasantly cool all night.

Highly recommended!

Hotel Shivkrupa is a clean, no-frills, family-friendly place that's great for a quick and satisfying meal. The atmosphere is simple and functional – nothing too fancy, but neatly maintained. Ideal for locals and travelers looking for a decent dining stop.

For non-veg lovers, the Chicken Thali is a must-try – good quantity and well-cooked with traditional spices.

Their chapatis are soft, and rice is perfectly steamed.

Staff is polite and quick. Food is served within 10–15 minutes, even during busy hours. They listen to requests and adjust spice levels if needed. Good for families, solo diners, and small groups.

🚗 Parking & Accessibility:
Limited parking, but manageable. Located on a main road, so it's easy to reach. Clean restrooms available.

✔ Authentic Maharashtrian taste
✔ Quick service
✔ Clean & budget-friendly
✔ Homely feel

❌ Cons:
✘ Limited menu for snacks or desserts
✘ Gets crowded during lunch hours

📌 Final Verdict:
Hotel Shivkrupa is a reliable spot for hearty, flavorful meals that won’t hurt your wallet. Perfect for everyday lunches or dinners when you’re craving something simple yet satisfying. A great local gem!

text.text:
Had a day stay here(4am-4pm).
Average stay.
Charged 1108 for 10-11 hours stay.

Pro
Staff is friendly and helpfulThere is a nice cute Labrador named Moti. Allowed entry in room at 05:00 amVery close to Railway station.
Around 1km walkable distance from station.
Has bisleri water on chargeable basis.Rooms and washroom were clean.
You get home cooked food tiffin for Rs.80
Hot water available till 9-10am. Post that staff provide hot water in bucket.Room has TV

Cons
Its a 90+ years old house turned into a hotel.
Rooms are very basic compared to the price.Rooms are congested.
Washroom is even more congested. Very small place to take bath.
During checkin we were asked to give only aadhar card without which entry was not allowed. This was not told in advance.As per the Hotel this is a requirement by Pune Police(police notice attached). Aadhar card is not a mandatory document. Its linked to bank accounts. Its not right on Pune Police behalf to demand the same.
If you are not comfortable sharing aadhar card with any unlicensed authority then this is not a place for you. Also check with other hotel before checking in if Aadhar is mandatory.Being close to Station no rickshaw drop you or picks you from here. Only option is booking rickshaw from Uber ola. Usually charged anywhere between 30-50 for drop to station. same for droping from station to hotel. At night or early morning the Richaw can demand 100-150 or simply reject taking you there. If you are young you can walk and reach here. or book it before hand.
No complimentary drinking water.
No kettle, tea/cofee sachets.

If you are coming by train try booking retiring room which would cost you like 1500 for 24 hours or 900 for 12 hours.
